Bottom line, Bzzat has 3 killer Bees.  the one in the Middle MUST be mezzed First off no matter what. this is the bee we fought first - and spawns the boss.  can't do that.  Mez that one and mez the one on the right.  The one on the Right spawns 3 wasps on death - each spawns a new one on death.  Same strategy as used on the peg/griffs.  AT tanks but doesn't kill the spawn.  The one on the left spawns 2 - that each spawn one.  Same strategy.<br>
<br>
Since the boss DTs ON spawn - we have a NON Aggro player - has NOT attacked the 2nd spawned bee --- SIT under the fight.  When the Bee is Killed and the queen spawns - she will DT the sitter as having the highest aggro - MAKE sure that no one else is sitting when she spawns.  Then Zerg nation the queen the same way as the KoS, SL, Master Yael.  She hits for 850 max BUT - she can miss a lot if your tanks are all level 60ish.  As a level 61 ranger - she missed me more than she hit me and only landed max melee on me once.  I am not afraid of this boss mob - she just caught us with our collective pants down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btribalfury31319.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzenkaremberune>Azzenkar Emberune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/14/03 3:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftribalfury31319frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=229.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PoS Friday 16 Feb 930-1AM / 2nd day Sat 8PM to midnight</span><hr size=1>  If all goes according to plan I should be able to make the times posted for a change. Count me in.<br>
