<br>
Read about the Wasp Isle.  Learn it, live it, love it.  Note that the giant Bixie boss uses a DISEASE based attack while all other wasps use a poison attack.<br>
<br>
Please BRING your DR and PR gear.  Magi can summon a 15PR range item, as well as a 5PR dagger or two if you need.<br>
<br>
THE most IMPORTANT thing here is to NOT lose which bee is which when we have them mezzed.  Be rdy to camp out here if things go sour, and even more importantly, if YOU have aggro behind the gear during a camp out, a la poFear, get away from the main camp.  If you were present last weekend, you know that the bees camping our bodies was a major hinderance to regrouping and we eventually had to end the raid because of it.<br>
<br>
Senton had the right idea by camping out when he did, and I applaud him for it.  Even tho the circumstances nullified his efforts, he did the right thing.  As per this guide, I recommend we have SOMEONE camp out at the beginning.  Preferably one who can both jumpstart the raid from a wipe and have an alt they can spy on us with during the attack.  Not camped out during the entire fight, but just for the big bee.  Also, I would like that person to already have looted a key but Serano/Pensfan can make final calls on the order of keys looted.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If it looks like things are going to fail, train stuff away to the opposite side of the isle. The splits have no home spot and will stay camping the corpse of whomever they killed last.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
One theme throughout the description of the wasp isle...<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Did you hear Bzzazzt Isle is hard? Have your CR plan ready.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
For the queen bee, the guide mentions this:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>For this fight, I recommend fighting in the middle of the isle, on the other side of the gears. The reason for this is that you have to have a VERY strong group to kill all 4 successive spawns in one fell swoop. This way if you do camp out, the dish area will be clear for CR.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
-------------------<br>
The sphinxe isle.  One thing I read in this guide I never thought of until know regarding ALL DT mobs.  Magi can summon staves with charges of cancel magic.  Having the recipient of a DT pull with one of these staves may be most beneficial.  In regards to the sphinxes since they are enchanters..this is definitely the way to go.<br>
<br>
hmmm, I have a thought.  Was looking here ~~&gt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pages.infinit.net/adorno/sky.html" target="top">Sky Write-up</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and I got to thinking about the keys to the sphinxe isle.  What if, at the very least, we got a necro and a cleric and/or one other their keys and if we wipe, they could summon the whole raid as per the Crown bridge discussed earlier?  Would this be feasible?  It would be expensive, but if we wiped hard enough, or found for whatever reason we didn't have the DPS needed to bring down a lvl 63 DT mob we could always just chain past them right?  Maybe I am missing a vital detail, but just a random thought that popped into my head while doing some more research. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=523387"> Baron Drannor Soulslinger, 58 Conjurer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
and alter egos... <br>
